he Regional Innovation Engines under and test beds under .section 19108 of this titlesection 19110 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The activities of the Department of Commerce under this division, including regional technology hubs under , as added by section 10621, the Manufacturing USA Program established under , and the Hollings Manufacturing Extension Partnership ().section 3722a of title 15section 278s(b)(1) of title 1515 U.S.C. 278k","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The activities of the Department of Energy in the key technology focus areas, including at the national laboratories, and at Federal laboratories, as defined in , and facilities and user facilities operated in partnership with such national laboratories or the Department of Energy.section 3703 of title 15","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any other program that the Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy determines involves research and development with respect to the key technology focus areas.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Report","label":"d Report","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"assess current level of efforts and characterize existing research infrastructure, as of the date of the review;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify potential areas of overlap or duplication with respect to the key technology focus areas; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F1%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify potential cross-agency collaborations and joint funding opportunities; and1So in original. The word “and” probably should not appear.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"submit a report regarding the review described in subparagraph (A) to Congress; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"seek stakeholder input and recommendations in the course of such review; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall carry out the annual reviews and updates required under .2section 19107(e) of this titleSo in original. The word “shall” probably should not appear.2","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Conflicts","label":"e Conflicts","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s19251","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs19251%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If any conflicts between Federal agencies arise while carrying out the activities under this section, the President shall make the final decision regarding resolution of the conflict.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
